Organized by Black Student Union, students, parents, teachers, alumni & supporters marched on 4 July, 2020 to bring awareness to racial biases and discrimination in the Lusher Charter School community.

Hundreds of protesters marched from the elementary school to the high school where they demanded the name of the charter school to be changed, listened to students and alumni speak, and finished with the Black National Anthem, "Lift Every Voice and Sing."

As colleges shift to academic models of on-line learning, admissions offices are also adjusting to appropriate social distancing protocols, in most cases promoting virtual tours of campus and augmenting technology-based methods to maintain contact with current seniors and future applicants.

To assist Lusher students with maintaining active and engaged college search processes, Team Guidance will provide web resources and advice, beginning with virtual tours of five colleges in the greater New Orleans area, now posted to the grade-specific GoogleClassrooms. More to come.

Be safe, wash your hands, maintain social distance, & reach-out if you have any questions.
